chart_description: This chart measures the latencies in seconds of data encryption key (DEK) generation operations. It is in alpha and only for informational purposes.

dimension_descriptions.bucket_+Inf: The number of observations that were unbounded (i.e., taking more time than any of the buckets measured).
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.000005: The number of observations that took 0.000005 seconds or less.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00001: The number of observations that took between 0.000005 and 0.00001 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00002: The number of observations that took between 0.00001 and 0.00002 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00004: The number of observations that took between 0.00002 and 0.00004 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00008: The number of observations that took between 0.00004 and 0.00008 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00016: The number of observations that took between 0.00008 and 0.00016 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00032: The number of observations that took between 0.00016 and 0.00032 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00064: The number of observations that took between 0.00032 and 0.00064 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00128: The number of observations that took between 0.00064 and 0.00128 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00256: The number of observations that took between 0.00128 and 0.00256 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.00512: The number of observations that took between 0.00256 and 0.00512 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.01024: The number of observations that took between 0.00512 and 0.01024 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.02048: The number of observations that took between 0.01024 and 0.02048 seconds.
dimension_descriptions.bucket_0.04096: The number of observations that took between 0.02048 and 0.04096 seconds.
